From Subject Re Owners Tankbag Suggestions Wanted Blaine Gardner writes In article Mar Marten writes I am looking for a new tank bag now and I wondered if you as follow owners could make some suggestions as to what has and has not worked for With the FJ's large flat gas tank I'd imagine that almost anything would Personally I'm quite happy with my Eclipse standard tank Me Even after I bought the piece Krauser Now and then DK puts them on sale for bux or so to clear out inventory but they never seem to to go They are the Volkswagens of tank bags I BTW the late Paul O' Neill showed me a trick with a pair of pliers that will extend their life When the zipper starts to separate behind the pull because of age and wear squash the pull body with the pliers just a bit to tighten it back I would have tossed my bag three years ago but this fixed it up and kept it secure and Chuck Rogers